INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("131","1","2012-11-07 18:25:44","2012-11-08 02:25:44","<div class=\"one-third first\"><a href=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/KO14-e1411370173336.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1467 size-medium\" title=\"KyleOleary\" src=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/KO14-e1411370173336-262x343.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Kyle O\'Leary\" width=\"262\" height=\"343\" /></a></div>
<div class=\"two-thirds\">

A graduate of Duquesne university, Kyle played three years of college tennis there, with 69 career wins and two years as team captain.

He spent his freshman year at the University of Hartford, playing both soccer and tennis.
<h4>Junior tennis.</h4>
As a junior, Kyle ranked as high as 130 in the U.S. and as high as #5 in the Missouri Valley – and competed at the Kalamazoo (Hard Court) and Clay Court Super Nationals.

At Lindbergh High, he was a four-time District champ in singles and, in doubles, teamed up with FRC\'s Kyle Tosie to reach the state finals.

<h4>Summers and other seasons.</h4>
In the summer, Kyle teaches at Bellerive Country Club in Ladue. In spring and fall, he\'s the Washington University men\'s assistant tennis coach.

Kyle holds a degree in business and sports marketing.

Around the club, he runs Ladies\' Play with the Pros and works with the Top Guns kids.

You can reach him <a href=\"mailto:kyleo@frontenactennis.com\">here</a> by email or at (314) 369-1153 by text.

