INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("159","1","2012-11-07 14:35:03","2012-11-07 20:35:03","<a href=\"http://frc-tennis.com/rusty-jones/rustyjones/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-57\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-57\" title=\"RustyJones\" src=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/RustyJones.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"343\" /></a>

Rusty joined FRC in November 2011, when he and his family moved to Town &amp; Country from the Tehachapi Mountains of south central California.

Ironically, Rusty played college golf after struggling to choose between his two favorite sports. But after he won a USTA singles tennis event in Calabasas, California, the hosting club\'s tennis director invited Rusty to teach professionally.

He never looked back.

Since 1988, Rusty has taught at prestigious country clubs across California, rising to the level of head pro at the home club of a young rising star named Sam Querry.

As a member of the California PRINCE Sports Advisory Staff, Rusty competed at Indian Wells in Prince\'s private events with ATP tour pros Juan Carlos Ferrerro, David Ferrer, Xavier Malisse and Guillermo Coria.

Certified P1 with the USPTA, Rusty holds a business degree and did his undergraduate work in English/Communications at California State University Northridge. He also wrote the book META Tennis: A Handbook for Folks not Necessarily Wimbledon Bound.

Rusty and his wife have two teenage daughters in school at The Principia.

