INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("1465","1","2014-09-21 18:43:18","2014-09-22 01:43:18","<div class=\"one-third first\"><a href=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Conley1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1474 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Conley1-275x343.jpg\" alt=\"photo: David Conley\" width=\"275\" height=\"343\" /></a></div>
<div class=\"two-thirds\">

If David was a little late getting back to St. Louis for the opening of our 2014-15 season, he had a pretty good excuse:

He was a line judge at the US Open.

A member of the Saint Louis Association of Tennis Officials since 2006, a credentialed line umpire/sectional chair umpire for the USTA and more recently a line and chair umpire for the International Tennis Federation, David officiates at tournaments all over the country.
<h3>Mostly, though, David loves teaching.</h3>
A full-time pro at Frontenac during the year, he\'s spent his summers at high-profile tennis programs from John Newcombe\'s Tennis Ranch in Texas to Meadowbrook Country Club here at home.

Starting in 2013, he has been the director of tennis at Warson Woods – and still taught with Mark McPhillips at the Highlands in Forest Park.

David holds an MBA from Missouri Baptist University and has worked in customer-facing roles for the Cardinals, the Rams and the Chaifetz Arena.

You can email him <a href=\"mailto:dave@frc-tennis.com\">here</a> or text him at (314) 707-3523.

</div>
