INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("543","1","2013-03-15 10:02:11","2013-03-15 16:02:11","[caption id=\"attachment_547\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"330\"]<a href=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Mateo.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-547 \" alt=\"Photo: Mateo Dalla Fontana\" src=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/Mateo-550x686.jpg\" width=\"330\" height=\"412\" /></a> Mateo Dalla Fontana, creator of the Frontenac Pro Doubles Classic.[/caption]

The Frontenac Pro Doubles Classic is the creation of former Frontenac pro and Argentine native Mateo Della Fontana.

In his honor, the Triple A Youth Foundation has established the Mateo Della Fontana Scholarship Fund to support his brainchild, the Frontenac Pro Doubles Classic, going forward, as well as the development of up-and-coming junior tennis players in the St. Louis area.
<h2>Your donation: tickets to the Festival.</h2>
This year, every $100 donation before May 15 will get two entry passes that are valid for the whole Festival weekend\'s tennis events – the Friday night and Saturday afternoon tournament and the Mats Wilander exhibition.

Your donation is tax-deductible through the Triple A Youth Foundation.

<a href=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/youth-foundation-blue.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-546\" alt=\"Logo-Triple A Youth Foundation\" src=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/youth-foundation-blue-550x233.png\" width=\"300\"  /></a>","The Mateo Dalla Fontana Scholarship Fund.","","publish","open","open","","the-mateo-dalla-fontana-scholarship-fund","","","2013-03-15 10:02:11","2013-03-15 16:02:11","","0","http://www.frontenactennis.com/?p=543","0","post","","0");
INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("557","1","2013-03-18 14:37:25","2013-03-18 20:37:25","[caption id=\"attachment_558\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"275\"]<a href=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/2012FRCDoubleswinners.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-558    \" alt=\"Photo- Dave Reinhart and Wynn Criswell\" src=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/2012FRCDoubleswinners-275x225.jpg\" width=\"275\" height=\"225\" /></a> Dave Reinhart and Wynn Criswell, winners of the 2012 Frontenac Doubles Classic.[/caption]

Founded in 2009 by Mateo Dalla Fontana, the Doubles Classic is a professional-caliber men\'s prize-money invitational that features the top 16 players in the St. Louis area.
<h3>The tennis event of the year.</h3>
A one-night event for its first four years, it has attracted a who\'s-who of St. Louis tennis. Beyond top area pros on the court, observers include longtime industry insiders, friends and family – and tennis fans from a 50-mile radius. The event seats more than 800 spectators at the Frontenac Racquet Club.
<h3>From one night to a weekend of tennis action.</h3>
2013 is the fifth annual competition – and will see the event grow to span two days, as one of two marquee events of the 2013 St. Louis Tennis Hall of Fame Festival. <a title=\"Wow! It’s Mats Wilander, here in St. Louis!\" href=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wow-its-mats-wilander-here-in-st-louis/\">The Festival also features Mats Wilander\'s WOW program and an exhibition match. </a>

Early rounds will start at 6:30 pm Friday, May 17 and end with the final at noon Saturday, May 18.
<h3>Previous winners.</h3>
Classic champions in years past have been:

<em>2009:</em> Jalal Chafai and Dani Adalberti.

<em>2010:</em> Terry Ward and Ken Nordheim.

<em>2011:</em> Kevin Lackey and Billy Gluck.

<em>2012:</em> Wynn Criswell and Dave Reinhart.","The Frontenac Pro Doubles Classic.","","publish","open","open","","the-frontenac-pro-doubles-classic","","","2013-03-18 14:37:25","2013-03-18 20:37:25","","0","http://www.frontenactennis.com/?p=557","0","post","","0");
