INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("2122","1","2016-10-30 21:49:43","2016-10-30 21:49:43","<div class=\"copy4\">
<p><a href=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/terry14-e1411765574443.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1513\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1513\" src=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/terry14-e1411765574443.jpg\" alt=\"Terry Ward\" width=\"813\" height=\"1016\" /></a></p>
<div class=\"one-half first\">
<div class=\"vidbox\">
<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/ePpXS_I_NDI?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0\" width=\"783\" height=\"440\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>
</div>
</div>
<p>Raised in St. Louis, Terry grew up competing in area events. He played college tennis at the University of San Diego, competed on the Pro Tour and achieved a world ranking in both singles and doubles in the early 1980s.</p>
<p>Back in St. Louis as of 1982, Terry was the Head Pro at Frontenac and the Tennis Director at Old Warson Country Club. Over the years, he\'s also served on a variety of boards for the St. Louis District Tennis Association and the National USTA.</p>
<p>Appointed manager at Frontenac in 2006, Terry continues his heavy involvement in the area tennis scene.</p>
<p>In summer he heads the Old Warson tennis program and organizes the Gateway Junior Novice Events. His very popular summer Junior Camp at Frontenac is full every week. Since 2013, Terry\'s arranged for Frontenac to run the Clayton-Shaw Park summer program.</p>
<p>On top of all that, Terry still finds time to coach tennis at John Burroughs School.</p>
<p>He and his wife, Jeannie, have five grown children. Their three sons are full-time pros here at Frontenac. </p>
</div>
