INSERT INTO `wp_dyfl_posts` VALUES("2145","1","2016-10-30 22:56:59","2016-10-30 22:56:59","<div class=\"copy4\"><a href=\"http://www.frctennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/tennis-portrait-e1444683995581.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1756 size-medium\" title=\"Chris Nasrallah\" src=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/tennis-portrait-247x343.jpg\" alt=\"Photo - Chris Nasrallah\" width=\"247\" height=\"343\" /></a></p>
<p>For a guy some of us only see a few times a week, Chris Nasrallah is one of the busiest pros on the FRC roster.

<p>Chris has been teaching tennis in the St. Louis area for more than 15 years. Here at Frontenac, he runs the men\'s (7:30-9) Saturday morning clinics. He\'s the Platform Tennis Director at Bellerive Country Club from October to February. Come summer, he\'s at Westwood Country Club with <a title=\"Stefan Kruger\" href=\"http://www.frontenactennis.com/stefan-kruger/\">Stefan</a>.</p>
<p>Need some equipment? Chris is an authorized Prince dealer in St. Louis and a member of the Prince Advisory Team. Finally, Chris is also the USTA Tennis On Campus Chairman for the Missouri Valley-St. Louis region.</p>
<p>(All this on top of a day job as a commercial real estate broker ...)</p>
<h3>Playing days.</h3>
<p>After a very promising junior career, Chris played Division 1 tennis at Bradley University in Peoria, IL.</p>
<p>At Chaminade, he was a Missouri state champion all four years he played — and won the individual doubles state title in 1991.</p>
<p>Overall, Chris was a top junior in St. Louis; he made the top 20 in the Missouri Valley and the top 200 nationally.</p>
<h3>Home and family.</h3>
<p>Chris and his wife, Angela, have two girls — Sophia, born in 2010, and Abigail, born in 2012.</p>
